The paper proposes an efficient CNN for real-time semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed method also involves the use of Class Boundary Supervision and Multi-features Fusion Module, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The task of semantic segmentation is relevant to robotics, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the proposed method achieves impressive results while maintaining high speed, which is related to multimedia processing, and hence cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
